{"text": " Where at war, the U.S. and Israel did a joint attack on Iran that killed a supreme leader over the weekend. Then what happened? Iran retaliated with the strikes targeting the U.S. military, allies in the Persian Gulf, and Israel. And what happens now? The U.S. has pledged to send more troops to the region, and the U.S. military said they expect more casualties. At the time of recording, six U.S. service members have died. How many people in Iran have died? It's hard to verify because communication from Iran is really restrictive. The state broadcaster reported over 500 people killed from the ongoing air strikes. Iran's ambassador to the U.N. said a strike on a girl's elementary school killed over 100 children in southern Iran. We know how long this will last. We know Trump has said four to five weeks, but we also know he said the U.S. has the capability to go far longer than that. Anything else? This isn't the first time the U.S. has removed the leader of a country. The U.S. usually follows it up with deploying thousands of troops and spending billions of dollars. But instead of peace, it usually leaves those states in conflict. What else should I know? A lot is happening. If you have questions you want answered in a future video, let me know in the comments. Because", "segments": [{"id": 0, "seek": 0, "start": 0.0, "end": 4.48, "text": " Where at war, the U.S. and Israel did a joint attack on Iran that killed a supreme leader over the weekend.", "tokens": [50364, 2305, 412, 1516, 11, 264, 624, 13, 50, 13, 293, 5674, 630, 257, 7225, 2690, 322, 8283, 300, 4652, 257, 27756, 5263, 670, 264, 6711, 13, 50588], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13903586669538007, "compression_ratio": 1.7146814404432134, "no_speech_prob": 0.03364928066730499}, {"id": 1, "seek": 0, "start": 4.48, "end": 5.2, "text": " Then what happened?", "tokens": [50588, 1396, 437, 2011, 30, 50624], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13903586669538007, "compression_ratio": 1.71468144044